# Progethod

A simplified timesheet interface for Wethod. Data is stored locally (localStorage) and synced to a backend API. Built with Nuxt 2 (SPA mode, static target) + Vuex + TailwindCSS.

## Architecture

- **Framework**: Nuxt 2 (Vue 2), SPA mode (`ssr: false`, `target: static`)
- **State**: Vuex modules persisted via `vuex-persist` to localStorage
- **Styling**: TailwindCSS with PostCSS
- **i18n**: `@nuxtjs/i18n`, Italian only (`locales/it.json`)
- **API**: Axios, backend at `/api/`
- **Calendar**: Google Calendar integration for importing events

## Vuex Modules

- `store/projects.js` — User-created local project shortcuts (aliases to Wethod projects/areas)
- `store/pills.js` — User-created note suggestions ("pills") shown when the notes field is empty
- `store/entries.js` — Daily timesheet entries
- `store/user.js` — Auth token, user info
- `store/apiData.js` — Cached Wethod project data
- `store/preferences.js` — UI preferences (confirm on submit, business unit filter)

## Key Decisions

- **Pills feature**: Global note suggestions (not project-scoped). Appear only when notes field is focused + empty. Keyboard navigation: ArrowDown enters pills mode, ArrowLeft/Right navigates, Enter selects, ArrowUp/Esc exits. Stored same as projects with soft-delete pattern.
- **Persistence**: All Vuex modules (including pills) persisted to localStorage. Soft-deleted items pruned after 40 days.
- **Sync**: Projects and pills sync to backend via PUT on mutation. Entries are local-only until explicitly submitted.
- **Keyboard navigation**: Full keyboard nav via `plugins/keyboard-shortcuts.js`. Global shortcuts only fire when user is not typing in an input.
